  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CELAM-DEJUSOL: Strenghtening the CLAMOR network (2019-2021)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">One of the great challenges for the Latin American and Caribbean Church is to coordinate and strengthen its pastoral work in providing care for migrants, refugees and victims of trafficking, particularly in the face of the unprecedented migratory crisis of Venezuelans, the caravans of Central American migrants heading towards the US, and the difficult situation of the Haitian people. Pope Francis has shown the path that the Church should take: &#x201C;embrace, protect, promote and integrate&#x201D;. 

Diverse bodies and organisations of the Catholic Church already carry out numerous actions to care for migrants, although these efforts are often undertaken in isolation, which affects the efficiency of the services that are being provided. For two years now, the CLAMOR network has been a space of coordination for the Latin American Church and organisations that work in the area of human mobility, promoting togetherness and participation. In the next three years (2019-2021), the CLAMOR network will promote opportunities to train pastoral facilitators, will disseminate a map of services that already exist in all Latin American countries in favour of migrants and refugees, will sensitise the Church and society in general to the &#x201C;culture of encounter and welcoming&#x201D;, and will strengthen advocacy processes. Another important task for the next three years will also be the dissemination of the agreements established in the Global Compact for Migration (2018), in order to influence governments to comply with them. Integral Ecology will be a cross-cutting approach in the pastoral care for migrants, since &quot;everything is interconnected&quot; (LS XX).</narrative>
  </description>
